{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"All buildings today have something in common."},{"time":4000,"text":"They're made using Victorian technologies."},{"time":7000,"text":"This involves blueprints,"},{"time":10000,"text":"industrial manufacturing"},{"time":12000,"text":"and construction using teams of workers."},{"time":15000,"text":"All of this effort results in an inert object."},{"time":18000,"text":"And that means that there is a one-way transfer of energy"},{"time":21000,"text":"from our environment into our homes and cities."},{"time":25000,"text":"This is not sustainable."},{"time":27000,"text":"I believe that the only way that it is possible for us"},{"time":30000,"text":"to construct genuinely sustainable homes and cities"},{"time":33000,"text":"is by connecting them to nature,"},{"time":35000,"text":"not insulating them from it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":38000,"text":"Now, in order to do this, we need the right kind of language."},{"time":42000,"text":"Living systems are in constant conversation"},{"time":44000,"text":"with the natural world,"},{"time":46000,"text":"through sets of chemical reactions called metabolism."},{"time":50000,"text":"And this is the conversion of one group of substances"},{"time":53000,"text":"into another, either through"},{"time":55000,"text":"the production or the absorption of energy."},{"time":58000,"text":"And this is the way in which living materials"},{"time":60000,"text":"make the most of their local resources"},{"time":63000,"text":"in a sustainable way."},{"time":66000,"text":"So, I'm interested in the use of"},{"time":68000,"text":"metabolic materials for the practice of architecture."},{"time":73000,"text":"But they don't exist. So I'm having to make them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":75000,"text":"I'm working with architect Neil Spiller"},{"time":77000,"text":"at the Bartlett School of Architecture,"},{"time":79000,"text":"and we're collaborating with international scientists"},{"time":81000,"text":"in order to generate these new materials"},{"time":83000,"text":"from a bottom up approach."},{"time":85000,"text":"That means we're generating them from scratch."},{"time":87000,"text":"One of our collaborators is chemist Martin Hanczyc,"},{"time":91000,"text":"and he's really interested in the transition from"},{"time":94000,"text":"inert to living matter."},{"time":96000,"text":"Now, that's exactly the kind of process that I'm interested in,"},{"time":99000,"text":"when we're thinking about sustainable materials."}]},{"cues":[{"time":101000,"text":"So, Martin, he works with a system called the protocell."},{"time":106000,"text":"Now all this is -- and it's magic --"},{"time":109000,"text":"is a little fatty bag. And it's got a chemical battery in it."},{"time":112000,"text":"And it has no DNA."},{"time":115000,"text":"This little bag is able to conduct itself"},{"time":117000,"text":"in a way that can only be described as living."},{"time":120000,"text":"It is able to move around its environment."},{"time":123000,"text":"It can follow chemical gradients."},{"time":125000,"text":"It can undergo complex reactions,"},{"time":128000,"text":"some of which are happily architectural."},{"time":132000,"text":"So here we are. These are protocells,"},{"time":134000,"text":"patterning their environment."},{"time":136000,"text":"We don't know how they do that yet."},{"time":139000,"text":"Here, this is a protocell, and it's vigorously shedding this skin."},{"time":143000,"text":"Now, this looks like a chemical kind of birth."},{"time":145000,"text":"This is a violent process."}]},{"cues":[{"time":148000,"text":"Here, we've got a protocell to extract carbon dioxide"},{"time":151000,"text":"out of the atmosphere"},{"time":153000,"text":"and turn it into carbonate."},{"time":155000,"text":"And that's the shell around that globular fat."},{"time":157000,"text":"They are quite brittle. So you've only got a part of one there."},{"time":160000,"text":"So what we're trying to do is, we're trying to push these technologies"},{"time":163000,"text":"towards creating bottom-up construction approaches"},{"time":165000,"text":"for architecture,"},{"time":167000,"text":"which contrast the current, Victorian, top-down methods"},{"time":170000,"text":"which impose structure upon matter."},{"time":173000,"text":"That can't be energetically sensible."}]},{"cues":[{"time":176000,"text":"So, bottom-up materials"},{"time":178000,"text":"actually exist today."},{"time":180000,"text":"They've been in use, in architecture, since ancient times."},{"time":183000,"text":"If you walk around the city of Oxford, where we are today,"},{"time":186000,"text":"and have a look at the brickwork,"},{"time":188000,"text":"which I've enjoyed doing in the last couple of days,"},{"time":190000,"text":"you'll actually see that a lot of it is made of limestone."},{"time":192000,"text":"And if you look even closer,"},{"time":194000,"text":"you'll see, in that limestone, there are little shells"},{"time":196000,"text":"and little skeletons that are piled upon each other."},{"time":199000,"text":"And then they are fossilized over millions of years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":202000,"text":"Now a block of limestone, in itself,"},{"time":204000,"text":"isn't particularly that interesting."},{"time":207000,"text":"It looks beautiful."},{"time":209000,"text":"But imagine what the properties of this limestone block might be"},{"time":213000,"text":"if the surfaces were actually"},{"time":215000,"text":"in conversation with the atmosphere."},{"time":218000,"text":"Maybe they could extract carbon dioxide."},{"time":221000,"text":"Would it give this block of limestone new properties?"},{"time":224000,"text":"Well, most likely it would. It might be able to grow."},{"time":227000,"text":"It might be able to self-repair, and even respond"},{"time":229000,"text":"to dramatic changes"},{"time":231000,"text":"in the immediate environment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":233000,"text":"So, architects are never happy"},{"time":236000,"text":"with just one block of an interesting material."},{"time":239000,"text":"They think big. Okay?"},{"time":241000,"text":"So when we think about scaling up metabolic materials,"},{"time":244000,"text":"we can start thinking about ecological interventions"},{"time":246000,"text":"like repair of atolls,"},{"time":248000,"text":"or reclamation of parts of a city"},{"time":251000,"text":"that are damaged by water."},{"time":253000,"text":"So, one of these examples"},{"time":255000,"text":"would of course be the historic city of Venice."},{"time":258000,"text":"Now, Venice, as you know, has a tempestuous relationship with the sea,"},{"time":262000,"text":"and is built upon wooden piles."},{"time":264000,"text":"So we've devised a way by which it may be possible"},{"time":267000,"text":"for the protocell technology that we're working with"},{"time":269000,"text":"to sustainably reclaim Venice."},{"time":272000,"text":"And architect Christian Kerrigan"},{"time":274000,"text":"has come up with a series of designs that show us"},{"time":276000,"text":"how it may be possible to actually grow a limestone reef"},{"time":279000,"text":"underneath the city."}]},{"cues":[{"time":281000,"text":"So, here is the technology we have today."},{"time":284000,"text":"This is our protocell technology,"},{"time":286000,"text":"effectively making a shell, like its limestone forefathers,"},{"time":290000,"text":"and depositing it in a very complex environment,"},{"time":293000,"text":"against natural materials."},{"time":295000,"text":"We're looking at crystal lattices to see the bonding process in this."},{"time":298000,"text":"Now, this is the very interesting part."},{"time":300000,"text":"We don't just want limestone dumped everywhere in all the pretty canals."},{"time":303000,"text":"What we need it to do is to be"},{"time":305000,"text":"creatively crafted around the wooden piles."}]},{"cues":[{"time":309000,"text":"So, you can see from these diagrams that the protocell is actually"},{"time":311000,"text":"moving away from the light,"},{"time":313000,"text":"toward the dark foundations."},{"time":315000,"text":"We've observed this in the laboratory."},{"time":317000,"text":"The protocells can actually move away from the light."},{"time":320000,"text":"They can actually also move towards the light. You have to just choose your species."},{"time":323000,"text":"So that these don't just exist as one entity,"},{"time":325000,"text":"we kind of chemically engineer them."},{"time":328000,"text":"And so here the protocells are depositing their limestone"},{"time":331000,"text":"very specifically, around the foundations of Venice,"},{"time":334000,"text":"effectively petrifying it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":336000,"text":"Now, this isn't going to happen tomorrow. It's going to take a while."},{"time":340000,"text":"It's going to take years of tuning and monitoring this technology"},{"time":344000,"text":"in order for us to become ready"},{"time":346000,"text":"to test it out in a case-by-case basis"},{"time":348000,"text":"on the most damaged and stressed buildings within the city of Venice."},{"time":351000,"text":"But gradually, as the buildings are repaired,"},{"time":354000,"text":"we will see the accretion of a limestone reef beneath the city."},{"time":357000,"text":"An accretion itself is a huge sink of carbon dioxide."},{"time":361000,"text":"Also it will attract the local marine ecology,"},{"time":364000,"text":"who will find their own ecological niches within this architecture."}]},{"cues":[{"time":368000,"text":"So, this is really interesting. Now we have an architecture"},{"time":371000,"text":"that connects a city to the natural world"},{"time":374000,"text":"in a very direct and immediate way."},{"time":376000,"text":"But perhaps the most exciting thing about it"},{"time":379000,"text":"is that the driver of this technology is available everywhere."},{"time":382000,"text":"This is terrestrial chemistry. We've all got it,"},{"time":385000,"text":"which means that this technology is just as appropriate"},{"time":388000,"text":"for developing countries as it is"},{"time":390000,"text":"for First World countries."},{"time":392000,"text":"So, in summary, I'm generating metabolic materials"},{"time":395000,"text":"as a counterpoise to Victorian technologies,"},{"time":398000,"text":"and building architectures from a bottom-up approach."}]},{"cues":[{"time":401000,"text":"Secondly, these metabolic materials"},{"time":403000,"text":"have some of the properties of living systems,"},{"time":405000,"text":"which means they can perform in similar ways."},{"time":408000,"text":"They can expect to have a lot of forms and functions"},{"time":411000,"text":"within the practice of architecture."},{"time":413000,"text":"And finally, an observer in the future"},{"time":416000,"text":"marveling at a beautiful structure in the environment"},{"time":419000,"text":"may find it almost impossible to tell"},{"time":422000,"text":"whether this structure"},{"time":424000,"text":"has been created by a natural process"},{"time":426000,"text":"or an artificial one."},{"time":428000,"text":"Thank you."},{"time":430000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}